00:00:01,960 --> 00:00:06,000
National Radio and Television Administration.

2
00:02:00,240 --> 00:02:02,320
Ladies and gentlemen,

3
00:02:03,000 --> 00:02:08,600
United Airlines flight UA087 to New York

4
00:02:08,919 --> 00:02:11,640
has now departed.

5
00:02:25,079 --> 00:02:25,960
I told you

6
00:02:26,800 --> 00:02:27,860
we'd never make it.

7
00:02:28,200 --> 00:02:34,200
I thought after all the changes in life,

8
00:02:35,079 --> 00:02:40,000
my heart would never race again.

9
00:02:42,240 --> 00:02:47,880
Yet I happened to meet you.

10
00:03:02,600 --> 00:03:03,560
I'm sorry.

11
00:03:03,560 --> 00:03:06,360
The number you have dialed is temporarily unavailable.

12
00:03:06,360 --> 00:03:07,760
Please try again later.

13
00:03:39,840 --> 00:03:40,480
Coming!

14
00:04:03,440 --> 00:04:04,040
Thank you.

15
00:04:06,440 --> 00:04:08,040
What would you like to drink?

16
00:04:10,800 --> 00:04:12,440
Anything is fine.

17
00:04:17,600 --> 00:04:19,399
You're still the same as before.

18
00:04:19,720 --> 00:04:21,450
Never can decide what to drink.

19
00:04:32,040 --> 00:04:33,920
By the way, Ruirui is asleep.

20
00:04:35,720 --> 00:04:38,080
She's been gloomy ever since she came back.

21
00:04:38,080 --> 00:04:39,409
Says she misses her dad.

22
00:04:39,480 --> 00:04:41,400
The school organized a summer camp.

23
00:04:41,400 --> 00:04:42,880
So I signed her up for it.

24
00:04:43,320 --> 00:04:44,880
I thought being with other kids

25
00:04:44,880 --> 00:04:46,210
might cheer her up a bit.

26
00:04:48,840 --> 00:04:49,800
Xiaqing.

27
00:04:51,960 --> 00:04:53,890
I'm really sorry to you and Ruirui.

28
00:04:54,640 --> 00:04:57,280
First time back in over three years,

29
00:04:58,159 --> 00:05:00,760
and I made you both unhappy. I'm sorry.

30
00:05:01,600 --> 00:05:03,200
Why so formal? We're family.

31
00:05:04,600 --> 00:05:05,240
Thank you.

32
00:05:13,440 --> 00:05:14,240
Have you

33
00:05:16,200 --> 00:05:17,720
told Wan Xinxin yet?

34
00:05:19,160 --> 00:05:19,840
No.

35
00:05:21,240 --> 00:05:23,300
How long are you planning to avoid it?

36
00:05:27,040 --> 00:05:28,320
I don't know.

37
00:05:28,480 --> 00:05:31,280
I just don't have the courage to tell her right now.

38
00:05:33,520 --> 00:05:35,600
What's your next step?

39
00:05:37,480 --> 00:05:39,880
I don't know. I'll take it one step at a time.

40
00:05:44,240 --> 00:05:45,300
Are you going back?

41
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:47,680
Maybe.

42
00:05:50,320 --> 00:05:51,159
Maybe not.

43
00:05:53,400 --> 00:05:54,320
Perhaps.

44
00:05:56,440 --> 00:05:58,480
Well, since Ruirui isn't here...

45
00:05:59,360 --> 00:06:01,560
I'll be going then.

46
00:06:01,800 --> 00:06:03,330
Where are you going so late?

47
00:06:05,560 --> 00:06:07,680
I booked a hotel before coming.

48
00:06:09,680 --> 00:06:10,720
What hotel?

49
00:06:13,320 --> 00:06:16,050
Will you sleep in Ruirui's room or the guest room?

50
00:07:04,600 --> 00:07:05,200
It's late.

51
00:07:09,160 --> 00:07:09,960
It's too late.

52
00:07:26,920 --> 00:07:29,180
Why did she only think about surgery now?

53
00:07:29,920 --> 00:07:30,450
Huaming.

54
00:07:31,200 --> 00:07:33,840
As a top neurosurgeon in the country,

55
00:07:34,680 --> 00:07:36,920
what do you think about this surgery

56
00:07:37,640 --> 00:07:39,640
and what are the chances of success?

57
00:07:40,400 --> 00:07:43,680
I'd say no more than 5 percent.

58
00:07:46,800 --> 00:07:48,280
Professor, you're right.

59
00:07:49,080 --> 00:07:50,159
Many experts in China

60
00:07:50,159 --> 00:07:51,560
are basically at a loss.

61
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:52,880
Since Mrs. Qin

62
00:07:52,880 --> 00:07:55,159
gave up her chance for treatment in America,

63
00:07:55,159 --> 00:07:56,880
could you possibly

64
00:07:56,880 --> 00:07:59,080
develop a special treatment plan here?

65
00:07:59,159 --> 00:08:02,220
The surgery would still need to be performed back home.

66
00:08:05,120 --> 00:08:05,880
Difficult.

67
00:08:07,600 --> 00:08:08,680
Really difficult.

68
00:08:10,680 --> 00:08:12,720
Professor, do you remember?

69
00:08:13,080 --> 00:08:14,640
When I was still a student,

70
00:08:15,360 --> 00:08:16,490
I truly regarded you

71
00:08:16,600 --> 00:08:18,200
as a god-like figure.

72
00:08:18,840 --> 00:08:22,000
You told me doctors aren't omnipotent.

73
00:08:22,560 --> 00:08:23,920
Not every life

74
00:08:23,920 --> 00:08:25,640
can be saved with certainty.

75
00:08:26,360 --> 00:08:28,080
But as long as there's even a 1 percent chance,

76
00:08:28,080 --> 00:08:29,410
we should never give up.

77
00:08:29,760 --> 00:08:32,820
That's what you taught me, and I remember it to this day.

78
00:08:37,280 --> 00:08:37,840
Huaming.

79
00:08:38,919 --> 00:08:41,179
Setting aside my role as your professor,

80
00:08:41,280 --> 00:08:44,039
we've been good friends for many years.

81
00:08:49,000 --> 00:08:51,000
I've always believed in you.

82
00:08:51,960 --> 00:08:53,960
I've treated you like my own child.

83
00:08:55,560 --> 00:08:58,080
I'll definitely help you with this.

84
00:08:59,960 --> 00:09:01,220
Thank you, Professor.

85
00:09:01,560 --> 00:09:02,200
Thank you.

86
00:09:22,320 --> 00:09:22,800
Sis.

87
00:09:23,920 --> 00:09:26,250
Xinxin, have you really decided to leave?

88
00:09:26,360 --> 00:09:28,720
Please look after the gallery for me these days.

89
00:09:28,720 --> 00:09:30,560
Don't be so impulsive, okay?

90
00:09:30,720 --> 00:09:32,040
I must go to America this time.

91
00:09:32,040 --> 00:09:33,240
I must find Huaming.

92
00:09:34,400 --> 00:09:35,320
You're crazy.

93
00:09:36,240 --> 00:09:38,280
Your English is terrible.

94
00:09:39,000 --> 00:09:40,520
You'll be in a completely foreign place.

95
00:09:40,520 --> 00:09:41,520
Someone could sell you off.

96
00:09:41,520 --> 00:09:43,040
And you'd be counting the money for them.

97
00:09:43,040 --> 00:09:44,720
I really can't worry about all that.

98
00:09:44,720 --> 00:09:46,400
I won't give up until I hit a dead end.

99
00:09:46,400 --> 00:09:47,480
I must find him.

100
00:09:47,680 --> 00:09:49,200
What about Bao?

101
00:09:49,480 --> 00:09:51,080
Are you just abandoning him?

102
00:09:51,360 --> 00:09:53,520
Bao is staying at Qin Gang's house these days.

103
00:09:53,520 --> 00:09:55,580
I'll be back as soon as possible, sis.

104
00:09:57,000 --> 00:09:59,000
There's something I've been meaning to tell you.

105
00:09:59,000 --> 00:10:00,200
But I haven't said it yet.

106
00:10:00,200 --> 00:10:01,720
Now I have no choice but to tell you.

107
00:10:01,720 --> 00:10:03,640
Sis, you don't need to say anything.

108
00:10:03,640 --> 00:10:05,040
I must go to America.

109
00:10:05,040 --> 00:10:06,040
Did you know

110
00:10:06,880 --> 00:10:08,600
Huaming met with Mrs. Qin?

111
00:10:09,280 --> 00:10:10,440
Yes, I know that.

112
00:10:11,600 --> 00:10:13,000
She gave him some money.

113
00:10:13,680 --> 00:10:15,160
I know that too.

114
00:10:15,680 --> 00:10:16,920
You already know all this?

115
00:10:16,920 --> 00:10:18,920
Huaming started a medical website.

116
00:10:19,040 --> 00:10:20,040
The old lady gave him some

117
00:10:20,040 --> 00:10:21,280
financial support.

118
00:10:22,280 --> 00:10:24,010
Then think about it carefully.

119
00:10:24,040 --> 00:10:26,200
Do you think she gave that money for nothing?

120
00:10:26,200 --> 00:10:28,040
Mrs. Qin is very calculating.

121
00:10:28,320 --> 00:10:30,250
She must have planned everything.

122
00:10:30,320 --> 00:10:32,240
Why wouldn't he develop his business in China?

123
00:10:32,240 --> 00:10:33,500
Why run off to America?

124
00:10:34,000 --> 00:10:35,520
I think even if you go to America,

125
00:10:35,520 --> 00:10:37,980
you definitely won't be able to see Huaming.

126
00:10:39,080 --> 00:10:40,600
Why don't you understand?

127
00:10:40,920 --> 00:10:42,850
She just wants to separate you two.

128
00:10:48,520 --> 00:10:49,120
All right.

129
00:10:51,120 --> 00:10:52,050
Let's go inside.

130
00:11:07,160 --> 00:11:07,800
Weimin.

131
00:11:07,920 --> 00:11:08,640
Huaming.

132
00:11:09,200 --> 00:11:10,200
Well,

133
00:11:11,400 --> 00:11:13,080
Professor Wei has already

134
00:11:13,080 --> 00:11:15,280
developed a surgical plan for Mrs. Qin.

135
00:11:16,080 --> 00:11:17,000
That's great!

136
00:11:18,600 --> 00:11:21,200
But will Mrs. Qin go to America for the surgery?

137
00:11:21,720 --> 00:11:22,480
Actually,

138
00:11:24,440 --> 00:11:26,160
I've convinced Professor Wei

139
00:11:26,640 --> 00:11:29,040
to come back to China to perform the surgery for Mrs. Qin.

140
00:11:29,040 --> 00:11:30,800
And also to provide

141
00:11:30,800 --> 00:11:33,860
some guidance for our hospital's future development.

142
00:11:34,040 --> 00:11:36,440
Professor Wei's return is wonderful news!

143
00:11:37,560 --> 00:11:40,090
When is he coming back? Let me know in advance.

144
00:11:40,320 --> 00:11:42,320
I need to make proper preparations.

145
00:11:42,360 --> 00:11:43,120
Weimin, there's no need.

146
00:11:43,120 --> 00:11:45,040
Just make sure all the necessary documents

147
00:11:45,040 --> 00:11:46,080
at the hospital are ready.

148
00:11:46,080 --> 00:11:48,400
Professor Wei is like family to us,

149
00:11:48,840 --> 00:11:50,160
so don't go to any trouble.

150
00:11:50,160 --> 00:11:52,160
Okay, I understand.

151
00:11:53,800 --> 00:11:55,560
But what about Mrs. Qin?

152
00:11:56,600 --> 00:11:59,480
Don't worry about that. I'll communicate with her in advance.

153
00:11:59,480 --> 00:12:01,210
I'll let you know ahead of time.

154
00:12:02,200 --> 00:12:02,840
Huaming.

155
00:12:03,840 --> 00:12:06,040
How are things going for you in America?

156
00:12:08,960 --> 00:12:10,890
I'll tell you when I get back, okay?

157
00:12:11,160 --> 00:12:13,220
That's all for now, Weimin. Goodbye.

158
00:12:21,880 --> 00:12:23,280
Little monkey.

159
00:12:23,480 --> 00:12:24,520
Hold it. Hold it.

160
00:12:24,520 --> 00:12:27,040
This is a monkey.

161
00:12:28,880 --> 00:12:30,320
Going grocery shopping.

162
00:12:31,440 --> 00:12:32,040
Auntie.

163
00:12:32,040 --> 00:12:32,920
Xinxin is here.

164
00:12:33,200 --> 00:12:35,560
I'd like to speak with you privately about something.

165
00:12:35,560 --> 00:12:36,240
Sure.

166
00:12:36,600 --> 00:12:38,640
Xiaogang, go upstairs first.

167
00:12:39,280 --> 00:12:41,120
Mom, why should I leave?

168
00:12:41,600 --> 00:12:44,160
Xinxin wants to talk to me privately. Go upstairs.

169
00:12:44,160 --> 00:12:45,120
Go on up.

170
00:12:46,520 --> 00:12:48,180
We're going upstairs to play.

171
00:12:48,240 --> 00:12:48,960
Let's go.

172
00:12:49,640 --> 00:12:50,770
Have a seat, Xinxin.

173
00:12:55,200 --> 00:12:55,840
Auntie.

174
00:12:56,200 --> 00:12:58,800
Why do you insist on breaking up me and Huaming?

175
00:12:59,240 --> 00:13:01,520
What did you do to make him go to America?

176
00:13:03,720 --> 00:13:05,520
Why are you bringing this up now?

177
00:13:06,160 --> 00:13:07,090
Isn't that true?

178
00:13:08,360 --> 00:13:09,760
When I asked you that day,

179
00:13:10,480 --> 00:13:12,520
you said you only gave him

180
00:13:12,520 --> 00:13:13,920
some financial support.

181
00:13:14,880 --> 00:13:16,840
Was it just financial support?

182
00:13:17,920 --> 00:13:19,800
His Huaming Online could be run from anywhere.

183
00:13:19,800 --> 00:13:21,720
Why did he have to go to America?

184
00:13:22,680 --> 00:13:24,840
Why did you have to separate us?

185
00:13:27,040 --> 00:13:29,520
I separated you?

186
00:13:30,680 --> 00:13:31,440
Xinxin,

187
00:13:32,280 --> 00:13:34,080
do you really think I would do

188
00:13:34,280 --> 00:13:35,800
something so terrible?

189
00:13:37,680 --> 00:13:38,940
Don't be silly, child.

190
00:13:40,000 --> 00:13:41,360
Huaming went to America

191
00:13:41,680 --> 00:13:43,600
for his own reasons.

192
00:13:44,440 --> 00:13:45,240
In America,

193
00:13:45,520 --> 00:13:48,380
he has his ex-wife and daughter that he can't let go.

194
00:13:48,800 --> 00:13:50,360
And he's always dreamed

195
00:13:50,360 --> 00:13:52,680
of his career as a doctor.

196
00:13:53,560 --> 00:13:55,000
Yes, I did give him some

197
00:13:55,000 --> 00:13:56,160
financial help.

198
00:13:56,240 --> 00:13:58,800
I wanted him to make Huaming Online better

199
00:13:58,800 --> 00:13:59,840
so more people

200
00:13:59,840 --> 00:14:02,040
could go to America for treatment.

201
00:14:02,680 --> 00:14:04,240
How did this become

202
00:14:04,680 --> 00:14:06,600
a reason for me to break you up?

203
00:14:06,960 --> 00:14:08,360
What a coincidence then.

204
00:14:09,520 --> 00:14:12,000
Why did you choose this exact time to return to China?

205
00:14:12,000 --> 00:14:13,200
Why did Huaming choose

206
00:14:13,200 --> 00:14:14,960
this exact time to go to America?

207
00:14:14,960 --> 00:14:16,920
I know in your eyes,

208
00:14:17,000 --> 00:14:18,930
anything can be solved with money.

209
00:14:19,480 --> 00:14:21,080
So you bribed him with money.

210
00:14:26,920 --> 00:14:27,720
Xinxin.

211
00:14:29,160 --> 00:14:31,620
You and Huaming aren't right for each other.

212
00:14:32,120 --> 00:14:34,480
Both of you once had

213
00:14:34,480 --> 00:14:36,640
very happy families.

214
00:14:36,640 --> 00:14:38,400
And you both have children.

215
00:14:38,400 --> 00:14:39,720
All of this can't be

216
00:14:39,720 --> 00:14:41,800
cut off so easily.

217
00:14:42,720 --> 00:14:44,840
Before going to America, you kept telling me

218
00:14:44,840 --> 00:14:46,600
that you wouldn't come back to disturb us.

219
00:14:46,600 --> 00:14:48,040
You gave your blessing to me and Huaming.

220
00:14:48,040 --> 00:14:49,770
Why did you go back on your word?

221
00:14:52,600 --> 00:14:53,160
I know.

222
00:14:53,760 --> 00:14:56,360
You just want me to remarry Qin Gang, don't you?

223
00:14:56,400 --> 00:14:57,460
But let me tell you,

224
00:14:57,880 --> 00:14:59,240
I will absolutely never

225
00:14:59,240 --> 00:15:01,170
remarry Qin Gang in this lifetime.

226
00:15:02,360 --> 00:15:04,220
Even if I don't stay with Huaming,

227
00:15:04,360 --> 00:15:06,090
I still won't remarry Qin Gang.

228
00:15:06,600 --> 00:15:08,160
But you can't

229
00:15:08,920 --> 00:15:10,800
abandon your son.

230
00:15:10,800 --> 00:15:13,160
You need to think about your baby.

231
00:15:13,960 --> 00:15:15,490
I am thinking about my baby.

232
00:15:15,800 --> 00:15:18,660
I don't want him to learn bad habits from his father.

233
00:15:20,200 --> 00:15:21,800
Alright, Xinxin.

234
00:15:21,960 --> 00:15:23,040
I can't discuss

235
00:15:23,120 --> 00:15:24,920
this issue with you anymore.

236
00:15:25,000 --> 00:15:26,880
Fine, let's not talk about it.

237
00:15:27,200 --> 00:15:29,460
If you don't want to remarry, then don't.

238
00:15:29,560 --> 00:15:31,800
But I think between you and Xiao Gang,

239
00:15:31,960 --> 00:15:33,880
couldn't you stop being

240
00:15:34,080 --> 00:15:35,920
so resentful toward each other?

241
00:15:36,160 --> 00:15:38,160
You were husband and wife after all.

242
00:15:38,160 --> 00:15:40,160
Even a day of marriage creates a bond that lasts.

243
00:15:40,160 --> 00:15:42,760
For the sake of your child,

244
00:15:42,920 --> 00:15:45,720
couldn't you understand and help each other?

245
00:15:45,760 --> 00:15:47,840
You can at least be family, can't you?

246
00:15:48,280 --> 00:15:50,680
I've always acknowledged that Xiaobao is Qin Gang's son.

247
00:15:50,680 --> 00:15:52,280
I also allow him to visit him.

248
00:15:53,400 --> 00:15:54,800
But I don't want to have

249
00:15:54,800 --> 00:15:56,960
any emotional entanglements with Qin Gang anymore.

250
00:15:56,960 --> 00:15:59,690
Fine, if there's nothing, then there's nothing.

251
00:15:59,920 --> 00:16:01,240
But there's one thing

252
00:16:01,240 --> 00:16:02,960
I must make clear to you.

253
00:16:03,280 --> 00:16:05,560
Xiaobao must stay with our Qin family.

254
00:16:05,560 --> 00:16:06,490
On what grounds?

255
00:16:06,760 --> 00:16:08,020
I am Xiaobao's mother.

256
00:16:08,360 --> 00:16:09,920
The court has already awarded Xiaobao to me.

257
00:16:09,920 --> 00:16:11,080
He is mine.

258
00:16:11,080 --> 00:16:13,360
I admit he is your child,

259
00:16:13,360 --> 00:16:14,280
but no matter what,

260
00:16:14,280 --> 00:16:17,210
he is also flesh and blood of our Qin family, isn't he?

261
00:16:17,800 --> 00:16:20,720
If he stays with our family, we can give him

262
00:16:20,720 --> 00:16:22,120
a better life,

263
00:16:22,120 --> 00:16:24,480
both in daily life and education.

264
00:16:24,480 --> 00:16:25,760
You are his mother.

265
00:16:25,760 --> 00:16:27,440
You can come see him whenever you want.

266
00:16:27,440 --> 00:16:29,520
But I think you should

267
00:16:32,400 --> 00:16:33,200
Auntie!

268
00:16:34,160 --> 00:16:35,600
No, Auntie!

269
00:16:36,000 --> 00:16:36,560
Auntie!

270
00:16:37,440 --> 00:16:38,560
Qin Gang

271
00:17:07,560 --> 00:17:08,440
Let me tell you something.

272
00:17:08,440 --> 00:17:09,960
If anything happens to my mother,

273
00:17:09,960 --> 00:17:11,079
I won't let this go.

274
00:17:11,319 --> 00:17:12,720
How could you be so cruel?

275
00:17:12,920 --> 00:17:14,160
Even if you don't like her,

276
00:17:14,160 --> 00:17:15,599
you shouldn't do this.

277
00:17:15,880 --> 00:17:18,160
No, I just...

278
00:17:18,160 --> 00:17:18,880
I didn't expect

279
00:17:18,880 --> 00:17:20,400
she would get so emotional.

280
00:17:20,400 --> 00:17:22,319
I really didn't mean to.

281
00:17:22,319 --> 00:17:23,359
